'''Olander Brit'''<ref name="CCG">{{CCG|set=Death Star II Limited|cardname=Major Olander Brit}}</ref> was a fair-skinned [[Human/Legends|Human]] with [[Color/Legends|brown]] [[Hair/Legends|hair]] who joined the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]]<ref name="ROTJ" /> by [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]],<ref name="FF">{{FactFile|66|DET 1-2|Detailing the Rebel Assault}}</ref> following [[Major/Legends|Major]] [[Panno]] to the Alliance.<ref name="CCG" /> He was a communications expert and was [[Politics/Legends|politically]] minded.<ref name="CSWE" /> By 4 [[Galactic Standard Calendar|ABY]],<ref name="FF" /> Brit was an Alliance major, with staff monitoring the entire [[Spectrum/Legends|spectrum]] of [[Electromagnet/Legends|electromagnetic]] signals.<ref name="CCG" />

In 4 ABY,<ref name="FF" /> shortly before the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]], Brit was aboard the [[MC80A Home One Type Heavy Star Cruiser/Legends|MC80 ''Home One'' type Star Cruiser]] [[Home One/Legends|''Home One'']], attending a briefing where the [[Alliance High Command/Legends|Alliance High Command]] planned an attack on the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire's]] [[Death Star II/Legends|second Death Star]] [[Battle station/Legends|battle station]]. Brit wore the standard [[Alliance Fleet/Legends|Alliance Fleet]] [[Officer/Legends|officer]] [[Alliance military uniform/Legends|uniform]].<ref name="ROTJ" /> 

==Behind the scenes==
Portrayed by an uncredited [[Peter Roy]],<ref name="Convention">{{WebCite|url=http://www.convention-guests.com/html/peter_roy.html|text=Peter Roy|work=convention-guests.com|archivedate=20100424040322}}</ref> Olander Brit first appeared in [[1983]]'s [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']], the third film of the [[original trilogy]].<ref name="ROTJ" /> His scenes were filmed throughout the week of Tuesday, [[February 16]], [[1982]] at Stage 5 of [[Elstree Studios]].<ref name="BTS">{{WebCite|url=https://swnz.co.nz/2017/03/11/gerald-home-tessek-squid-head-mon-calamari-officer-2|text=Gerald Home as Tessek (Squid Head) and Mon Calamari Officer|author=G., Matt|date=2004-06-11|work=[https://swnz.co.nz Star Wars New Zealand]|archiveurl=https://archive.vn/JbkiZ}}</ref> In [[2000]], [[Decipher]] first named Brit in the [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game's]] ''[[Death Star II Limited]]'' expansion set.<ref name="CCG" />

